metadata.name: Mini Dahlias #11
metadata.description:
Welcome to the enchanting world of "Mini Dahlias" - a mesmerizing generative art project that will spark joy in your heart! Unleashing the magic of algorithms, each miniature masterpiece blooms with vibrant colors and whimsical patterns, transporting you to a dreamy realm of creativity.

But wait, there's more to this fantastical journey! Nestled within each digital artwork lies a hidden treasure - an embedded blueprint that holds the secret to crafting a tangible, real-life edition. Picture it: delicate petals brought to life in the physical realm, ready to be gifted or cherished!

Twenty exquisite physical editions of ‚Äúmini Dahlias,‚Äù crafted with love are destined to be gifted by a friend of mine to random strangers at Burning Man, where creativity knows no bounds!

Inspired by spreading joy and creativity, "Mini Dahlias" is available on fxhash, ensuring that this delightful experience can be enjoyed by art enthusiasts worldwide. metadata.name: Garden, Monoliths #228
metadata.description:
"Garden, Monoliths" is the result of an algorithm that started in April 2021. It was called "Grass.js".
Spring was blooming all around the house, taking over the stones and remnants of ancient battles that stood here. Inspiration was everywhere.
The initial goal was to use mathematical formulas for creating patterns inspired by the density of nature, that could be used by a pen plotter, so it kept focusing on outputting vector lines. This history and practice produced a graphical style based on line strokes, plus occasionally some transparent, filled shapes.
Each artwork will be either "Garden" or "Monolith", for they are variations of two existing designs from the workshop.

metadata.name: Liny_Dancers #34
metadata.description:
Liny_Dancers.
I wrote four lines.

The simple shapes reminded me of people are dancing.
I enjoyed it and felt happy again.

I wanted a result quite minimally.
I wanted to cram in all kinds of ideas.
But I decided against it.

The maximum number of dancers would be five dancers.

But the more dancers, It will be Rare.

I feel joy, emotion, and melancholy from the way they dance.

Please enjoy it.

metadata.name: Sketches:Pairs of Tails:Majestic Creatures #29
metadata.description:
Addendum to Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

There is a significantly common phenomena in which Pairs of "Tails of Majestic Creatures" are found together. Various sketches of these "Pairs" have been collated and are available, free of charge, the collectors of the initial Tails of Majestic Creatures collection based upon a recently taken collection registry snapshot. 

These sketches are available on a one per collector basis and for a limited time only after which they will no longer be accessible.

The sketches come in 2 forms - an ink and color style, and a pencil style - for which different colored paper has been used.

The digitally minded can press s to get a 5000x3000 download of a sketch.

metadata.name: Cube on Cube #60
metadata.description:
This token generates a plottable SVG file, a different arrangement of cubes.
The cubes are designed in 2D view, then placed next to each other or on top of each other in eight different directions. The goal is to challenge the audience's mind to discover the holes or protrusions produced by placing the cubes together.
To produce random parts made of cubes, those in the same direction are merged together, which is a turning point in this project.
Do you need a different output from your piece?  Then use controllers!

Controllers 
G - Change light direction
F - Add/remove frame
L - Add/remove base lines
D - Change base lines direction
R - Reset to default settings
P - Save as PNG
S - Export high resolution SVG

Note : When you have a piece with many shapes, controllers may run delayed. (Depending on your device).

Made by p5.js
